name: Region
description: Geographic-cultural classification, created in the following hierarchy: Region/Division/Subregion/Area. Area could also be interpreted as Kingdom

name: Division
description: Geographic-cultural classification, created in the following hierarchy: Region/Division/Subregion/Area. Area could also be interpreted as Kingdom

name: Subregion
description: Geographic-cultural classification, created in the following hierarchy: Region/Division/Subregion/Area. Area could also be interpreted as Kingdom

name: Area/Kingdom
description: Geographic-cultural classification, created in the following hierarchy: Region/Division/Subregion/Area. Area could also be interpreted as Kingdom

name: Culture
description: Prefered name of a culture

name: Alt_culture_names
description: Alternative name for a culture

name: People
description: People:  Ethnographic Atlas, GlobalJB

name: People2
description: Larger cultural grouping encompassing People1. Not finalized or completed yet.

name: Arensberg-Lomax_clusters
description: Categories relating to a clustering analyses performed in Lomax, A. (1989). Cantometrics. In International encyclopedia of communications (1st ed., pp. 230–233). New York, NY: Oxford University Press.

name: Focal_years
description: Year or decade to which song and culture data pertain.

name: C_sample_size
description: The number of songs in Cantometrics for a culture

name: Koppen_climate_terrain
description: Climate category based on Koppen-Geiger World Maps http://koeppen-geiger.vu-wien.ac.at/. Multiple categories are comma separated.

name: Koppen_code
description: Climate category code based on Koppen-Geiger World Maps http://koeppen-geiger.vu-wien.ac.at/. Multiple categories are comma separated.

name: Arensberg/Lomax_taxon
description: Taxon allocations from Lomax, A., & Arensberg, C. M. (1977). A Worldwide Evolutionary Classification of Cultures by Subsistence Systems. Current Anthropology, 18(4), 659–708.

name: Taxon_id
description: Refined Arensberg-Lomax Culture ID, from Lomax & Arensberg (1977).

name: Language
description: Primary language spoken by a culture

name: Lang_Family
description: The language family linked to a culture

name: Lang_Family_Tree
description: The hierarchy of language families linked to a culture

name: ISO_code
description: ISO 639 is a standardized nomenclature used to classify languages

name: Glottocode
description: Identification code based on Glottolog.org

name: Country
description: Name of the country a culture resides in. If a culture persists across borders, countries are seperated by semi-colons.

name: All_cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture

name: C_cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture in Cantometrics

name: M_cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture in Minutage

name: Ch_cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture in Choreometrics

name: P_cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture in Parlametrics

name: Ph_cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture in Phonotactics

name: I+cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture in Instrument & Ensembles

name: Soc_cid
description: Unique identifier for each culture in XXXX

name: D-Place_Id
description: Unique identifier for pairing data to D-PLACE (d-place.org)

name: People/Culture
description: Notes about a culture
